[SourceTitle "02 Alapin Variation"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "black-vs-anti-sicilians-tournament-edition/course/2385, variation/79699"]

1. e4 c5 2. c3 Nf6 {This is my favorite line. It is also the most common.} 3. e5 
Nd5 4. Nf3 {This is a less common move order.} e6 5. Bc4 {This is a sideline 
which usually transposes.} d6 6. d4 cxd4 7. cxd4 Nc6 {White cannot permanently 
double Black's pawns with Bxd5 because the pawns will be undoubled with an 
eventual dxe5.} 8. O-O Be7 9. Qe2 O-O 10. Nc3 Nxc3 11. bxc3 dxe5 12. dxe5 {Black 
has a better pawn structure but a badly placed bishop on c8} Qa5 {Black 
activates his queen.} *

