5. cxd4 {Qxd4 will be explored in another variation.} d6 {Black tries to break 
up White's pawns.} 6. Nf3 e6 7. Bc4 Nc6 {The game has now transposed to the 
previous variation.} 8. O-O Be7 9. Qe2 O-O 10. Nc3 Nxc3 11. bxc3 dxe5 12. dxe5 
Qa5 *

