1. e4 c5 2. c3 Nf6 3. e5 Nd5 4. d4 cxd4 5. Qxd4 {This sideline is played 
occasionally.} e6 {Supporting the knight.} 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. Qe4 {This thought to be 
the best square for the queen in this variation.} f5 $1 {An aggressive line that 
gives Black excellent play.} 8. Qe2 {exf6 e.p. is met by Nxf6 with tempo as 
well.} Qc7 {Black puts pressure on White's pawn on e5.} 9. g3 b5 $1 {This is a 
nice move.} 10. Bg2 {Qxb5 gives Black an edge after Nxe5.} a5 {Black expands 
further on the queenside.} 11. O-O Ba6 {Black has an amazing position. His 
pieces are very active and he has good winning chances.} *

