on the pawn.} e6 6. cxd4 d6 {We have now transposed to previous variations.} 7. 
a3 {This is a sideline that White can try.} Bd7 8. Bd3 Bc6 {Black has maneuvered 
his light-squared bishop to its most active post on c6.} 9. O-O Nd7 {Black is 
putting serious pressure on White's center and can continue to develop 
naturally.} *

