9. Be3 Nd4 10. Bf2 {White retreats the bishop, avoiding potential forks.} Nec6 
11. e5 dxe5 12. Nxe5 Nxe5 13. fxe5 Bxe5 {Black has an extra pawn, but White has 
strong bishops and an open f-file to work with. I prefer Black's position 
however.} *

