1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 g6 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. Bc4 d6 6. O-O e6 7. d3 Nge7 8. Qe1 
O-O 9. f5 gxf5 10. Qh4 {White brings his queen to h4 instead of g3.} fxe4 11. 
Ng5 {This aggressive move is now possible.} h6 {Now White has several 
scary-looking moves such as Ncxe4 or Nxf7. However, Black is up a pawn and 
objectively clearly better. At the master level, this position scores much 
better for Black.} *

