1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 g6 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. Bb5 Nd4 6. O-O {This is the main 
line.} a6 7. Bc4 e6 {This move has many purposes. It controls the d5-square, 
frees the e7-square for Black's knight, and limits the power of White's 
light-squared bishop.} 8. a4 Ne7 9. e5 d5 {This is a very powerful move. White 
is basically forced to take the pawn via e.p.} 10. exd6 Qxd6 {Black's position 
is quite comfortable.} *

