1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 g6 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. Bb5 Nd4 6. O-O a6 7. Bd3 {White 
chooses to retreat the bishop to d3 instead of c4.} d6 8. Nxd4 cxd4 9. Ne2 Nf6 
10. Kh1 {This move frees the g1-square. If he chooses, White might play Rg1 
followed by g4.} Nd7 {Black develops naturally.} 11. b4 {White tries to take 
away the excellent c5-square from Black's knight.} O-O 12. Bb2 Qb6 {Black will 
eventually support his pawn on d4 with e7-e5 if possible.} *

