[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "black-vs-anti-sicilians-tournament-edition/course/2385, variation/79773"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nc6 4. Bxc6+ {White can choose to trade on c6. This 
usually works in Black's favor.} bxc6 5. O-O e5 {This stops White from playing 
e4-e5 himself.} 6. c3 Nf6 {Black is doing a good job of controlling the center.} 
7. Re1 Bg4 8. h3 Bxf3 9. Qxf3 Be7 {A slow, positional game will probably ensue. 
Black's position is quite good.} *

