[SourceTitle "07 Chekhover Variation"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "black-vs-anti-sicilians-tournament-edition/course/2385, variation/79763"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Qxd4 {This is called the Chekhover Variation.} 
Nc6 {Black can take advantage of White's exposed queen by developing with 
tempo.} 5. Bb5 Bd7 {Black breaks the pin.} 6. Qd3 {This is the most common 
sideline.} Nf6 7. c4 {establishing a maroczy bind} g6 8. Nc3 Bg7 9. O-O O-O 
{Both sides have developed naturally. One plan for Black is to control the 
c-file with his rooks and then play a6 followed by an eventual b7-b5, opening 
the c-file.} *

